Program: Outlook
Title: My Childhood in a Mexican Prison
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03rjksg
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 28 Apr 2016
Pedro Martín Núñez was just two-years-old when he ended up in one of Mexico's most notorious prisons with his mother. Hear how he managed to escape a life of crime. Outlook Inspirations is our search for 50 of the world's most inspiring people, and it is all in honour of Outlook's 50th birthday this July. Nunu Ntshingila is one of the judges. She is the head of Facebook for Africa and has a long background in business and marketing. The closing date for all nominations is the 1 May. The Irish band The Corrs have sold over 40 million albums worldwide. And, it is all in the family, because the band is made up of the sisters Sharon, Caroline and Andrea Corr, and their older brother Jim. Now, after more than 10 years off, they are back with a new album. (Picture: Topo Chico prison. Credit: Julio Cesar Aguilar/AFP/Getty Images) Show less